tel=E2=80=99s contract manufacturing plans:

Without Tower, Intel, historically a maker of its own chips, lacks the expe=
rtise to work with external customers, which it has struggled to attract, a=
ccording to four sources familiar with Intel=E2=80=99s manufacturing busine=
ss. Tan grew frustrated as the board did not follow his recommendations ove=
r how to make the manufacturing business more customer-centric and to remov=
e unnecessary bureaucracy, a person close to Tan said.

