Venu, though, wasn=E2=80=99t one company offering a product it controlled; =
it was a joint venture between horizontal competitors colluding to offer a =
product that they refused to make available to other competitors in the dis=
tribution layer. Collusion is illegal, and Fubo, which would like nothing m=
ore than to offer nothing but sports channels, was right to sue for being e=
xcluded from doing just that, and I agree with the judge that they are like=
ly to win at trial.

